Sandostatin (octreotide acetate) is a synthetic analogue of somatostatin, which has a long duration of action and is used pharmacologically to reduce blood glucose levels. It inhibits the release of insulin and glucagon, as well as the absorption of glucose in the stomach and small intestine.
